# The BayesDiffIRT for R

The `BayesDiffIRT` provides functions to sample posterior distributions and posterior predictive distributions of item and subject parameters of diffusion item response theory models for responses and reaction times [@molenaar_fitting_2015, @van_der_maas_cognitive_2011, @tuerlinckx_two_2005]  `BayesDiffIRT` also provides functions to visualize posterior distributions of Diffusion item response theory model parameters and construct HDIs. Under the hood, the package relies on NUTS with STAN [@carpenter_stan_2017]. Up to know, the following diffusion item response theory models have been implemented: 

* D-Diffusion model [@tuerlinckx_two_2005],
* Q-Diffusion model [@van_der_maas_cognitive_2011].


# Mathematical description of diffusion item response theory models
All models included in the `BayesDiffIRT` package are all based on the drift diffusion model of decision making [@stone_models_1960; @link_sequential_1975; @Ratcliff2016]. 

To visualize the resulting reaction time distributions, interactive tools such as the [diffusion model visualizer](https://osf.io/4en3b) are openly available [@alexandrowicz_diffusion_2020]. 

